{
  "doc_id": "36844",
  "text": "Also, the various types of photoinitiators have been found to affect the degree of cure. TPO molecules showed higher degree of cure than CQ/amine [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] especially when cured by dual peak LED LCUs [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] PPD showed no significant difference in the degree of cure compared to CQ when cured with a LED LCU but not with a QTH LCU when it showed a lower degree of cure [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] . PPD, when used in combination with CQ, resulted in a higher degree of cure compared to each of them when used alone [CITATION_9] . However Brandt [CITATION_10] found no difference in the degree of cure when using PPD/CQ together, or each one separately.",
